HEADWORD: Dispermous
<hw>Di*sper"mous</hw> <pr>(d⟦isl⟧*sp⟦etil⟧r"m⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>di-</grk> = <grk>dis</grk> + <grk>spe`rma</grk> seed, fr.
<grk>spei`rein</grk> to sow: cf. F. <ets>disperme</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Containing only two seeds; two-seeded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

